55 “O brother, I see now,” said he, “the knot 56 that held the Notary and Guittone and me 57 from here from the sweet new style that I hear!
58 I see well how your pens 59 go closely behind the dictator, 60 which did not happen to ours certainly;
61 and whoever puts himself more to please beyond, 62 no longer sees from one style to the other”; 63 and, as if content, he became silent.

