query.result:
76 “I do not know,” I replied to him, “how long I live;
77 but already it will not be my returning soon,
78 unless my will brings me first to the shore;

79 because the place where I was placed to live,
80 from day to day more of good is stripped,
81 and seems prepared for sad ruin.”

112 Then he departed as if having changed his mind;
113 and we came to the great tree now,
114 that rejects so many prayers and tears.

118 Thus among the branches someone said, I do not know who;
119 for which Virgil and Statius and I, constrained,
120 went beyond to the side that rises.

