query.result:
136 I raised my head to see who it was;
137 and never were seen in a furnace
138 glasses or metals so shining and red,

139 as I saw one who said: “If it pleases you
140 to climb upwards, here one must turn;
141 from here goes whoever wants to go for peace.”

142 His appearance had taken away my sight;
143 for I turned behind my teachers,
144 as a man who goes according to what he hears.

